<DOC><DOCNO> AP900719-0077 </DOCNO><FILEID>AP-NR-07-19-90 1214EDT</FILEID><FIRST>r i AM-BRF--Drug-Cigarettes     07-19 0105</FIRST><SECOND>AM-BRF--Drug-Cigarettes,0108</SECOND><HEAD>Swiss Court: Cigarettes Are Not Drugs</HEAD><DATELINE>LAUSANNE, Switzerland (AP) </DATELINE><TEXT>   A chain smoker may be addicted, butcigarettes are not drugs, according to the Swiss Supreme Court.   The Federal Tribunal's ruling upheld a lower court which ordereda health insurance company to pay $12,850 in sick benefits to aheavy smoker who had fallen ill.   The insurers had refused payment, arguing that their contractdid not provide for sick-benefit money for illnesses caused byabusive use of drugs or medicines.   In the ruling published Thursday, the Federal Tribunal saidwhile smoking may lead to addiction, cigarettes cannot be legallycategorized as drugs.</TEXT></DOC>